Hi, and welcome to Line Sheet, live from Los Angeles. It=E2=80=99s
Martin Luther King Jr. Day here in the United States, and President Donald =
Trump was inaugurated for a second time this morning. I hope everyone is ab=
le to take some time for themselves today.

Fashion keeps moving. (We=E2=80=99re already past Pitti Uomo and deep in th=
e Milan men=E2=80=99s shows, with Paris and Couture next.) I=E2=80=99ve got=
 some news from Chanel headquarters, notes on Taylor Swift=E2=80=99s drab
game-time look, a couple Cond=C3=A9 Nast updates, intel on who=E2=80=99s lo=
oking after Ivanka Trump=E2=80=99s and Usha Vance=E2=80=99s wardrobes, and =
a digression on the role that fashion might play in Hollywood=E2=80=99s fut=
ure. Not sure, however, if I have any words for Lauren S=C3=A1nchez=E2=80=
=99s exposed bra-top at the inauguration.=C2=A0

